3. Insecure Data Handling:
            In this room, you’ll explore 3 OWASP Top 10:2025 elements that arise from how applications handle user
input and data:


• A04 – Cryptographic Failures: 
                    Weak or incorrect use of encryption exposing sensitive data.
• A05 – Injection:   
                    Flaws that allow attackers to send malicious input, manipulating queries or commands.
• A08 – Software or Data Integrity Failures: 
                    Risks from tampered or unverified code, files, or data.


You’ll learn the theory behind these vulnerabilities, how to prevent them, and get hands-on experience by practicing
